<plot>What are the Odds? is the charming story of two young mathematicians who come to New York City for a conference and keep bumping into each other. Through mathematics, they determine that their repeated encounters must be the work of fate, but is it? This short film, shot in Manhattan on 16mm film, is a delightful tribute to New York City, to the romantic order of the universe, and to those forces that even mathematics can't explain.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?651483</url></doc>
